22#include <sys/cdefs.h>
23#ifndef lint
24__RCSID("$NetBSD: print-null.c,v 1.8 2017/09/08 14:01:13 christos Exp $");
25#endif
26
27/* \summary: BSD loopback device printer */
28
29#ifdef HAVE_CONFIG_H
30#include "config.h"
31#endif
32
33#include <netdissect-stdinc.h>
34
35#include <string.h>
36
37#include "netdissect.h"
38#include "af.h"
39
40/*
41 * The DLT_NULL packet header is 4 bytes long. It contains a host-byte-order
42 * 32-bit integer that specifies the family, e.g. AF_INET.
43 *
44 * Note here that "host" refers to the host on which the packets were
45 * captured; that isn't necessarily *this* host.
46 *
47 * The OpenBSD DLT_LOOP packet header is the same, except that the integer
48 * is in network byte order.
49 */
50#define NULL_HDRLEN 4
51
52/*
53 * Byte-swap a 32-bit number.
54 * ("htonl()" or "ntohl()" won't work - we want to byte-swap even on
55 * big-endian platforms.)
56 */
57#define SWAPLONG(y) \
58((((y)&0xff)<<24) | (((y)&0xff00)<<8) | (((y)&0xff0000)>>8) | (((y)>>24)&0xff))
59
60static inline void
61null_hdr_print(netdissect_options *ndo, u_int family, u_int length)
62{
63 if (!ndo->ndo_qflag) {
64 ND_PRINT((ndo, "AF %s (%u)",
65 tok2str(bsd_af_values,"Unknown",family),family));
66 } else {
67 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s",
68 tok2str(bsd_af_values,"Unknown AF %u",family)));
69 }
70
71 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", length %u: ", length));
72}
73
74/*
75 * This is the top level routine of the printer. 'p' points
76 * to the ether header of the packet, 'h->ts' is the timestamp,
77 * 'h->len' is the length of the packet off the wire, and 'h->caplen'
78 * is the number of bytes actually captured.
79 */
80u_int
81null_if_print(netdissect_options *ndo, const struct pcap_pkthdr *h, const u_char *p)
82{
83 u_int length = h->len;
84 u_int caplen = h->caplen;
85 u_int family;
86
87 if (caplen < NULL_HDRLEN) {
88 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[|null]"));
89 return (NULL_HDRLEN);
90 }
91
92 memcpy((char *)&family, (const char *)p, sizeof(family));
93
94 /*
95 * This isn't necessarily in our host byte order; if this is
96 * a DLT_LOOP capture, it's in network byte order, and if
97 * this is a DLT_NULL capture from a machine with the opposite
98 * byte-order, it's in the opposite byte order from ours.
99 *
100 * If the upper 16 bits aren't all zero, assume it's byte-swapped.
101 */
102 if ((family & 0xFFFF0000) != 0)
103 family = SWAPLONG(family);
104
105 if (ndo->ndo_eflag)
106 null_hdr_print(ndo, family, length);
107
108 length -= NULL_HDRLEN;
109 caplen -= NULL_HDRLEN;
110 p += NULL_HDRLEN;
111
112 switch (family) {
113
114 case BSD_AFNUM_INET:
115 ip_print(ndo, p, length);
116 break;
117
118 case BSD_AFNUM_INET6_BSD:
119 case BSD_AFNUM_INET6_FREEBSD:
120 case BSD_AFNUM_INET6_DARWIN:
121 ip6_print(ndo, p, length);
122 break;
123
124 case BSD_AFNUM_ISO:
125 isoclns_print(ndo, p, length);
126 break;
127
128 case BSD_AFNUM_APPLETALK:
129 atalk_print(ndo, p, length);
130 break;
131
132 case BSD_AFNUM_IPX:
133 ipx_print(ndo, p, length);
134 break;
135
136 default:
137 /* unknown AF_ value */
138 if (!ndo->ndo_eflag)
139 null_hdr_print(ndo, family, length + NULL_HDRLEN);
140 if (!ndo->ndo_suppress_default_print)
141 ND_DEFAULTPRINT(p, caplen);
142 }
143
144 return (NULL_HDRLEN);
145}
